<ol>
<li><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/y/</span> is rounded and is heard only in the Old Colony and Bergthal groups.</li>
<li><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/æ/</span> is an allophone of <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/a/</span> preceding an <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/l/</span> or a palatal consonant.<sup class="Template-Fact" style="white-space:nowrap;">[<i><a href="Wikipedia_Citation_needed" title="Wikipedia:Citation needed"><span title="This claim needs references to reliable sources from August 2012">citation needed</span></a></i>]</sup></li>
